{
  "local_port": 59836,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What do you put in a resignation letter?",
  "response": "A resignation letter is a formal way to notify your employer of your decision to leave your job. It should be concise, professional, and include the following key elements:\n\n### 1. **Header**\n   - Your name, address, and contact information\n   - Date of writing the letter\n   - Employer\u2019s name, title, and company address\n\n### 2. **Salutation**\n   - Address your employer or supervisor formally (e.g., \"Dear [Manager's Name]\")\n\n### 3. **Opening Statement**\n   - Clearly state your intention to resign.\n   - Mention your current position and the company.\n   - Example: \"I am writing to formally resign from my position as [Job Title] at [Company Name], effective [Last Working Day, typically two weeks from the date of the letter].\"\n\n### 4. **Reason (Optional)**\n   - You may briefly mention the reason for your resignation, but this is not required. Keep it positive or neutral.\n   - Example: \"I have accepted a new opportunity that aligns with my career goals.\" Or \"I\u2019ve decided to focus on personal development at this time.\"\n\n### 5. **Expression of Gratitude**\n   - Thank your employer for the opportunity and experience gained.\n   - Example: \"I am grateful for the support and opportunities I\u2019ve received during my time at [Company Name].\"\n\n### 6. **Transition Offer**\n   - Offer to assist with the transition, such as training a replacement or completing pending tasks.\n   - Example: \"I am happy to assist with the transition process to ensure a smooth handover of my responsibilities.\"\n\n### 7. **Closing Statement**\n   - End on a positive note.\n   - Example: \"I wish the company continued success in the future.\"\n\n### 8. **Sign-Off**\n   - Use a formal closing, such as \"Sincerely\" or \"Best regards.\"\n   - Include your full name and signature.\n\n---\n\n### Example Resignation Letter:\n\n**[Your Name]**  \n[Your Address]  \n[City, State, ZIP Code]  \n[Email Address]  \n[Phone Number]  \n[Date]  \n\n**[Manager\u2019s Name]**  \n[Company Name]  \n[Company Address]  \n[City, State, ZIP Code]  \n\n**Dear [Manager\u2019s Name],**  \n\nI am writing to formally resign from my position as [Job Title] at [Company Name], effective [Last Working Day].  \n\nThis decision was not an easy one, as I have greatly enjoyed working with the team and contributing to the company\u2019s success. However, I have decided to pursue a new opportunity that aligns with my long-term career goals.  \n\nI am deeply grateful for the support and opportunities I\u2019ve received during my time at [Company Name]. I\u2019ve learned a great deal and will always value the professional relationships I\u2019ve built here.  \n\nTo ensure a smooth transition, I am happy to assist in training a replacement or completing any outstanding projects over the next two weeks. Please let me know how I can be of help during this time.  \n\nThank you once again for the opportunity to be a part of [Company Name]. I wish the company and my colleagues continued success in the future.  \n\n**Sincerely,**  \n[Your Full Name]  \n\n---\n\nKeep the tone professional and avoid negativity or criticism, as you may need a reference from your employer in the future.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
